open&#10;&#10;@throws RuntimeException When proc_open is not installed&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="132" lineend="159" name="__construct" signature="__construct(string $commandline, string $cwd = null, array $env=null, string $stdin = null, integer $timeout = 60, array $options=array())"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="132" name="commandline" /><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="132" name="cwd" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="132" name="env" /><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="132" name="stdin" /><variable citdl="integer" default="60" ilk="argument" line="132" name="timeout" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="132" name="options" /></scope><scope attributes="public" ilk="function" line="161" lineend="165" name="__destruct" signature="__destruct()" /><scope attributes="public" ilk="function" line="167" lineend="179" name="__clone" signature="__clone()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Runs the process.&#10;&#10;The callback receives the type of output (out or err) and&#10;some bytes from the output in real-time. It allows to have feedback&#10;from the independent process during execution.&#10;&#10;The STDOUT and STDERR are also available after the process is finished&#10;via the getOutput() and getErrorOutput() methods.&#10;&#10;@param callback|null $callback A PHP callback to run whenever there is some&#10;                               output available on STDOUT or STDERR&#10;&#10;@return integer The exit status code&#10;&#10;@throws RuntimeException When process can't be launch or is stopped&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="200" lineend="205" name="run" returns="integer" signature="integer run($callback = null)"><variable default="null" ilk="argument" line="200" name="callback" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Starts the process and returns after sending the STDIN.&#10;&#10;This method blocks until all STDIN data is sent to the process then it&#10;returns while the process runs in the background.&#10;&#10;The termination of the process can be awaited with wait().&#10;&#10;The callback receives the type of output (out or err) and some bytes from&#10;the output in real-time while writing the standard input to the process.&#10;It allows to have feedback from the independent process during execution.&#10;If there is no callback passed, the wait() method can be called&#10;with true as a second parameter then the callback will get all data occurred&#10;in (and since) the start call.&#10;&#10;@param callback|null $callback A PHP callback to run whenever there is some&#10;                               output available on STDOUT or STDERR&#10;&#10;@throws RuntimeException When process can't be launch or is stopped&#10;@throws RuntimeException When process is already running" ilk="function" line="228" lineend="329" name="start" signature="start($callback = null)"><variable default="null" ilk="argument" line="228" name="callback" /><variable citdl="fread()" line="315" name="data" /><variable citdl="strlen()" line="277" name="stdinLen" /><variable citdl="this.getDescriptors()" line="240" name="descriptors" /><variable line="287" name="e" /><variable line="289" name="n" /><variable citdl="this.pipes" line="285" name="r" /><variable citdl="array()" line="275" name="writePipes" /><variable citdl="array_search()" line="314" name="type" /><variable citdl="writePipes" line="286" name="w" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="258" name="pipe" /><variable citdl="this.commandline" line="242" name="commandline" /><variable citdl="int" line="278" name="stdinOffset" /><variable citdl="fwrite()" line="303" name="written" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Restarts the process.&#10;&#10;Be warned that the process is cloned before being started.&#10;&#10;@param callable $callback A PHP callback to run whenever there is some&#10;                          output available on STDOUT or STDERR&#10;&#10;@return Process The new process&#10;&#10;@throws \RuntimeException When process can't be launch or is stopped&#10;@throws \RuntimeException When process is already running&#10;&#10;@see start()" ilk="function" line="346" lineend="356" name="restart" returns="Process" signature="Process restart(callable $callback = null)"><variable citdl="callable" default="null" ilk="argument" line="346" name="callback" /><variable citdl="this" line="352" name="process" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Waits for the process to terminate.&#10;&#10;The callback receives the type of output (out or err) and some bytes&#10;from the output in real-time while writing the standard input to the process.&#10;It allows to have feedback from the independent process during execution.&#10;&#10;@param callback|null $callback A valid PHP callback&#10;&#10;@return integer The exitcode of the process&#10;&#10;@throws \RuntimeException When process timed out&#10;@throws \RuntimeException When process stopped after receiving signal" ilk="function" line="372" lineend="454" name="wait" returns="integer" signature="integer wait($callback = null)"><variable default="null" ilk="argument" line="372" name="callback" /><variable citdl="this.pipes" line="383" name="r" /><variable citdl="fread()" line="405" name="data" /><variable citdl="array_search()" line="404" name="type" /><variable citdl="int" line="431" name="time" /><variable line="384" name="w" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="403" name="pipe" /><variable citdl="proc_close()" line="437" name="exitcode" /><variable line="385" name="e" /><variable line="388" name="n" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the Pid (process identifier), if applicable.&#10;&#10;@return integer|null The process id if running, null otherwise&#10;&#10;@throws RuntimeException In case --enable-sigchild is activated" ilk="function" line="463" lineend="472" name="getPid" returns="integer" signature="integer getPid()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sends a posix signal to the process.&#10;&#10;@param  integer $signal A valid posix signal (see http://www.php.net/manual/en/pcntl.constants.php)&#10;@return Process&#10;&#10;@throws LogicException   In case the process is not running&#10;@throws RuntimeException In case --enable-sigchild is activated&#10;@throws RuntimeException In case of failure" ilk="function" line="484" lineend="499" name="signal" returns="Process" signature="Process signal(integer $signal)"><variable citdl="integer" ilk="argument" line="484" name="signal" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the current output of the process (STDOUT).&#10;&#10;@return string The process output&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="508" lineend="513" name="getOutput" returns="string" signature="string getOutput()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the output incrementally.&#10;&#10;In comparison with the getOutput method which always return the whole&#10;output, this one returns the new output since the last call.&#10;&#10;@return string The process output since the last call" ilk="function" line="523" lineend="531" name="getIncrementalOutput" returns="string" signature="string getIncrementalOutput()"><variable citdl="this.getOutput()" line="525" name="data" /><variable citdl="substr()" line="527" name="latest" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the current error output of the process (STDERR).&#10;&#10;@return string The process error output&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="540" lineend="545" name="getErrorOutput" returns="string" signature="string getErrorOutput()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the errorOutput incrementally.&#10;&#10;In comparison with the getErrorOutput method which always return the&#10;whole error output, this one returns the new error output since the last&#10;call.&#10;&#10;@return string The process error output since the last call" ilk="function" line="556" lineend="564" name="getIncrementalErrorOutput" returns="string" signature="string getIncrementalErrorOutput()"><variable citdl="this.getErrorOutput()" line="558" name="data" /><variable citdl="substr()" line="560" name="latest" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the exit code returned by the process.&#10;&#10;@return integer The exit status code&#10;&#10;@throws RuntimeException In case --enable-sigchild is activated and the sigchild compatibility mode is disabled&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="575" lineend="584" name="getExitCode" returns="integer" signature="integer getExitCode()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns a string representation for the exit code returned by the process.&#10;&#10;This method relies on the Unix exit code status standardization&#10;and might not be relevant for other operating systems.&#10;&#10;@return string A string representation for the exit status code&#10;&#10;@see http://tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/exitcodes.html&#10;@see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix_signal" ilk="function" line="597" lineend="602" name="getExitCodeText" returns="string" signature="string getExitCodeText()"><variable citdl="this.getExitCode()" line="599" name="exitcode" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Checks if the process ended successfully.&#10;&#10;@return Boolean true if the process ended successfully, false otherwise&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="611" lineend="614" name="isSuccessful" returns="Boolean" signature="Boolean isSuccessful()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns true if the child process has been terminated by an uncaught signal.&#10;&#10;It always returns false on Windows.&#10;&#10;@return Boolean&#10;&#10;@throws RuntimeException In case --enable-sigchild is activated&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="627" lineend="636" name="hasBeenSignaled" returns="Boolean" signature="Boolean hasBeenSignaled()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the number of the signal that caused the child process to terminate its execution.&#10;&#10;It is only meaningful if hasBeenSignaled() returns true.&#10;&#10;@return integer&#10;&#10;@throws RuntimeException In case --enable-sigchild is activated&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="649" lineend="658" name="getTermSignal" returns="integer" signature="integer getTermSignal()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns true if the child process has been stopped by a signal.&#10;&#10;It always returns false on Windows.&#10;&#10;@return Boolean&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="669" lineend="674" name="hasBeenStopped" returns="Boolean" signature="Boolean hasBeenStopped()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the number of the signal that caused the child process to stop its execution.&#10;&#10;It is only meaningful if hasBeenStopped() returns true.&#10;&#10;@return integer&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="685" lineend="690" name="getStopSignal" returns="integer" signature="integer getStopSignal()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Checks if the process is currently running.&#10;&#10;@return Boolean true if the process is currently running, false otherwise" ilk="function" line="697" lineend="706" name="isRunning" returns="Boolean" signature="Boolean isRunning()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Checks if the process has been started with no regard to the current state.&#10;&#10;@return Boolean true if status is ready, false otherwise" ilk="function" line="713" lineend="716" name="isStarted" returns="Boolean" signature="Boolean isStarted()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Checks if the process is terminated.&#10;&#10;@return Boolean true if process is terminated, false otherwise" ilk="function" line="723" lineend="728" name="isTerminated" returns="Boolean" signature="Boolean isTerminated()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Gets the process status.&#10;&#10;The status is one of: ready, started, terminated.&#10;&#10;@return string The current process status" ilk="function" line="737" lineend="742" name="getStatus" returns="string" signature="string getStatus()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Stops the process.&#10;&#10;@param integer|float $timeout The timeout in seconds&#10;@param integer       $signal  A posix signal to send in case the process has not stop at timeout, default is SIGKILL&#10;&#10;@return integer The exit-code of the process&#10;&#10;@throws RuntimeException if the process got signaled" ilk="function" line="754" lineend="789" name="stop" returns="integer" signature="integer stop($timeout = 10, integer $signal = null)"><variable default="10" ilk="argument" line="754" name="timeout" /><variable citdl="integer" default="null" ilk="argument" line="754" name="signal" /><variable citdl="int" line="759" name="time" /><variable citdl="proc_close()" line="776" name="exitcode" /><variable citdl="int" line="756" name="timeoutMicro" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="780" name="fileHandle" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="771" name="pipe" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Adds a line to the STDOUT stream.&#10;&#10;@param string $line The line to append" ilk="function" line="796" lineend="799" name="addOutput" signature="addOutput(string $line)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="796" name="line" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Adds a line to the STDERR stream.&#10;&#10;@param string $line The line to append" ilk="function" line="806" lineend="809" name="addErrorOutput" signature="addErrorOutput(string $line)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="806" name="line" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Gets the command line to be executed.&#10;&#10;@return string The command to execute" ilk="function" line="816" lineend="819" name="getCommandLine" returns="string" signature="string getCommandLine()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the command line to be executed.&#10;&#10;@param string $commandline The command to execute&#10;&#10;@return self The current Process instance" ilk="function" line="828" lineend="833" name="setCommandLine" returns="self" signature="self setCommandLine(string $commandline)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="828" name="commandline" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Gets the process timeout.&#10;&#10;@return integer|null The timeout in seconds or null if it's disabled" ilk="function" line="840" lineend="843" name="getTimeout" returns="integer" signature="integer getTimeout()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the process timeout.&#10;&#10;To disable the timeout, set this value to null.&#10;&#10;@param float|null $timeout The timeout in seconds&#10;&#10;@return self The current Process instance&#10;&#10;@throws InvalidArgumentException if the timeout is negative" ilk="function" line="856" lineend="873" name="setTimeout" returns="self" signature="self setTimeout($timeout)"><variable ilk="argument" line="856" name="timeout" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Enables or disables the TTY mode.&#10;&#10;@param boolean $tty True to enabled and false to disable&#10;&#10;@return self The current Process instance" ilk="function" line="882" lineend="887" name="setTty" returns="self" signature="self setTty(boolean $tty)"><variable citdl="boolean" ilk="argument" line="882" name="tty" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Checks if  the TTY mode is enabled.&#10;&#10;@return Boolean true if the TTY mode is enabled, false otherwise" ilk="function" line="894" lineend="897" name="isTty" returns="Boolean" signature="Boolean isTty()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Gets the working directory.&#10;&#10;@return string The current working directory" ilk="function" line="904" lineend="914" name="getWorkingDirectory" returns="string" signature="string getWorkingDirectory()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the current working directory.&#10;&#10;@param string $cwd The new working directory&#10;&#10;@return self The current Process instance" ilk="function" line="923" lineend="928" name="setWorkingDirectory" returns="self" signature="self setWorkingDirectory(string $cwd)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="923" name="cwd" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Gets the environment variables.&#10;&#10;@return array The current environment variables" ilk="function" line="935" lineend="938" name="getEnv" returns="array" signature="array getEnv()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the environment variables.&#10;&#10;An environment variable value should be a string.&#10;If it is an array, the variable is ignored.&#10;&#10;That happens in PHP when 'argv' is registered into&#10;the $_ENV array for instance.&#10;&#10;@param array $env The new environment variables&#10;&#10;@return self The current Process instance" ilk="function" line="953" lineend="964" name="setEnv" returns="self" signature="self setEnv(array $env)"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="953" name="env" /><variable line="959" name="key" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="956" name="value" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Gets the contents of STDIN.&#10;&#10;@return string The current contents" ilk="function" line="971" lineend="974" name="getStdin" returns="string" signature="string getStdin()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the contents of STDIN.&#10;&#10;@param string $stdin The new contents&#10;&#10;@return self The current Process instance" ilk="function" line="983" lineend="988" name="setStdin" returns="self" signature="self setStdin(string $stdin)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="983" name="stdin" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Gets the options for proc_open.&#10;&#10;@return array The current options" ilk="function" line="995" lineend="998" name="getOptions" returns="array" signature="array getOptions()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the options for proc_open.&#10;&#10;@param array $options The new options&#10;&#10;@return self The current Process instance" ilk="function" line="1007" lineend="1012" name="setOptions" returns="self" signature="self setOptions(array $options)"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" 